.TH "LIGHTNING-ADDRESS" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-address \- Lightning Address (LUD-16) management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning address
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning address — Lightning Address (LUD-16) management.

Implements FEAT-176. Apache is the single supported host:
`address create` detects apache2, drops the Python CGI
handler under .well-known/lnurlp/, and registers the
<user>->account binding in the SQLite users table.
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning address <subcommand>

   resolve <addr>                          fetch LUD-06 metadata
   pay <addr> <sat> [--comment <text>]     send a LUD-06 payment
   create <user@domain> [--account <n>]    publish your own address
   list                                    your published addresses
   remove <user@domain>
   apache-snippet                          emit a drop-in vhost snippet
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
